r 3-8 hours[L9413] while intravenous solutions have an effective half life of 5 minutes and an elimination half life of 2.5 hours.[A187379,L9416] Patients taking ophthalmic formulations of phenylephrine should be counselled about the risk of arrhythmia, hypertension, and rebound miosis.[L9413] Patients taking an intravenous formulation should be counselled regarding the risk of bradycardia, allergic reactions, extravasation causing necrosis or tissue sloughing, and the concomitant use of oxytocic drugs.[L9416,L9410]', 'DrugBank', 0, 0, 0);
